[04_prepare_reference_broad_downsample.py]

Command:
python cell2location_run/scripts/04_prepare_reference_broad_downsample.py

Purpose:
Prepare a broad adult skin reference AnnData using raw counts and downsample large cell types.

Input file:
reference_atlas/adult_skin_atlas.h5ad

Output file:
cell2location_run/processed/ref_broad_adult_downsample.h5ad

labels_key:
annotation_broad_adult

Downsampling parameter:
max_cells_per_type: 5000
random_state: 0

Reason for downsampling:
The original reference contains 197812 cells x 36611 genes.
To reduce computation time, memory/GPU usage, and avoid dominance by very large cell types, each broad cell type was capped at 5000 cells.
Cell types with fewer than 5000 cells were fully retained.

Original adata:
(197812, 36611)

raw exists:
True

Important correction:
The original adata.X contained log-normalized expression values.
Raw count data were found in adata.raw.X.
adata.raw.X was used to construct the final reference AnnData for RegressionModel training.

Original filtered reference using raw counts:
(197812, 36611)

